A '''corticolous lichen''' is a [[lichen]] that grows on bark.<ref name=ASLGAF>Alan Silverside's Lichen Glossary (a-f), Alan Silverside, [http://www.lichens.lastdragon.org/faq/glossary1.html]</ref> This is contrasted with a [[lignicolous lichen]] that grows on wood that has had the bark stripped from it,<ref name=ASLGGO>Alan Silverside's Lichen Glossary (g-o), Alan Silverside, [http://www.lichens.lastdragon.org/faq/glossary2.html]</ref> and [[saxicolous lichen]]s that grow on rock.<ref name=ASLGPZ>Alan Silverside's Lichen Glossary (p-z), Alan Silverside, [http://www.lichens.lastdragon.org/faq/glossary3.html]</ref>

